description._content: Catalog #: 09_00982 Title: Colonel Cleon Eugene Freeman Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Aerial review aboard the Coral Sea during Shake Down Cruise, Cleon Freeman was a Captain of the 110th Air Corps Observation Squadron during World War II and served as a liaison officer between the Ninth Air Force and ground forces working in England. He was awarded the Croix de Guerre in 1940 and the Bronze Star Medal in 1944, Tags: Colonel Cleon Eugene Freeman Special Collection Photo,Â 1948 Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
